message: Focus on 'soft' items. Cutting any soft item (paper, leaf, sunflower, feather, newspaper, ribbon) gives 25 points. DO NOT cut 'hard' items (rock, acorn, pinecone, beads) as it results in negative value. The highest score (80) comes from combining an 'artificial, soft, cut' item with a 'natural, soft, cut' item (e.g., cut paper + cut leaf/sunflower). If you can't make that combination, combining two 'soft, cut' items of the same type (both natural or both artificial) yields 50. You can then use the 'frame' tool on a 50-point item to increase its value to 70, but 80 is better without framing.

message: To reach 100 points, consistently use 'scissors' on soft ingredients first. Prioritize combining a 'cut' item that is 'natural' and 'soft' with a 'cut' item that is 'artificial' and 'soft' to get 80 points.
